title: House and Senate to vote on Biden-McCarthy debt limit deal
description: President Biden and House Speaker McCarthy agreed on a deal to raise the debt ceiling but now it has to pass in both the House and Senate. NBC News’ Ryan Nobles has more details on members from both sides expressing their concerns about the legislation.

title: Chinese jet flew past nose of U.S. plane, says Pentagon
description: A Chinese fighter jet flew directly in front of the nose of a U.S. plane over the South China Sea, said the Pentagon, one of a rising number of incidents.

title: Teen fatally shot in back by S.C. store owner who wrongly accused him of shoplifting, sheriff says
description: A 14-year-old was fatally shot in the back Sunday by a South Carolina convenience store owner who wrongly accused him of shoplifting and chased him after a confrontation, authorities said.

title: Tennessee woman missing after starting cross-country trip with boyfriend, authorities say
description: Authorities are searching for a Tennessee woman who has been missing for weeks after allegedly setting off on a cross-country trip with her boyfriend, who was accused of punching her earlier this month, in a case that chillingly echoes the 2021 disappearance of Gabby Petito.

title: Natalee Holloway case suspect Joran van der Sloot injured in Peruvian prison brawl, lawyer says
description: The Dutch man who was among the last to see Natalee Holloway before she vanished was injured in a prison brawl as he awaits extradition to the United States, his Peruvian lawyer said Tuesday.

title: Former first lady Rosalynn Carter is diagnosed with dementia
description: Former first lady Rosalynn Carter has dementia, the Carter Center said Tuesday.

title: 5 people unaccounted for in partially collapsed Iowa apartment complex, 2 believed to still be in building
description: Five people are unaccounted for after a historic Iowa apartment building partially collapsed, and officials said Tuesday that two of them are believed to still be inside the building.

title: Marines and group of teens brawl on California pier over Memorial Day weekend, officials say
description: Deputies in Southern California said they are investigating a fight over Memorial Day weekend that involved several Marines and numerous juveniles and young adults.

title: ChatGPT cited 'bogus' cases for a New York federal court filing. The attorneys involved may face sanctions.
description: Roberto Mata’s lawsuit against Avianca Airlines wasn’t so different from many other personal injury suits filed in New York federal court.

title: AI risks leading humanity to 'extinction,' experts warn
description: Many of the biggest names in artificial intelligence have signed a short statement warning that their technology could spell the end of the human race.

title: Ralph Yarl, Black teen shot for ringing the wrong doorbell, walks at brain injury event
description: Ralph Yarl — a Black teenager who was shot in the head and arm after mistakenly ringing the wrong doorbell — walked at a brain injury awareness event in his first major public appearance since the shooting.

title: U.S. Coast Guard searching for man who fell overboard from Carnival cruise ship near Florida
description: The U.S. Coast Guard is searching for a 35-year-old man who fell overboard while on a Carnival cruise ship near Florida on Monday, according to a statement.

title: Far-right members, unhappy with debt deal, float threatening McCarthy's speakership
description: Some Freedom Caucus members have floated ousting Speaker Kevin McCarthy over his debt ceiling deal with President Joe Biden, or threatening to.

title: Chipmaker Nvidia hits $1 trillion market capitalization
description: Nvidia hit a $1 trillion market capitalization at the open of trading in U.S. markets Tuesday, joining a small club of mostly technology companies.

title: Debt ceiling deal faces first major test in House Rules Committee
description: Joe Biden and Speaker Kevin McCarthy's debt ceiling bill will face its first big test with the House Rules Committee’s expected vote on the measure Tuesday.

title: Chinese apps remain hugely popular in the U.S. despite efforts to ban TikTok
description: For several years now, ByteDance’s TikTok has been the focus of lawmakers and intelligence officials who fear it could be used to spy on Americans.

title: Elon Musk meets Chinese foreign minister, who calls for ‘mutual respect’ in U.S. relations
description: China’s foreign minister met Tesla CEO Elon Musk on Tuesday and said strained U.S.-Chinese relations require “mutual respect,” while delivering a message of reassurance that foreign companies are welcome.

title: Disgraced Theranos founder Elizabeth Holmes set to report to prison to begin 11-year sentence
description: Elizabeth Holmes, the founder of blood lab Theranos who became the face of Silicon Valley duplicity after her company collapsed amid fraud claims, is scheduled to report to prison Tuesday to begin her sentence of more than 11 years.

title: Drones attack Moscow residential areas for first time since Russia invaded Ukraine
description: Moscow was attacked with drones Tuesday morning, Russian officials said, as Kyiv was hit by Russian missile attacks.

title: Woman rescued uninjured 24 hours after Iowa building's partial collapse
description: After a  woman was pulled unscathed Monday evening from a partially collapsed Davenport, Iowa, apartment building, the  mayor said a plan to quickly tear down the structure was "under evaluation."

title: Man who crashed U-Haul truck near White House wanted to end U.S. democracy, prosecutors say
description: The man who  crashed a box truck into barriers near the White House planned to give a speech announcing the end of U.S. democracy, prosecutors said.
